<% provide(:title, 'Sign Up') %>
<h1>Sign Up</h1>

<div class="row">
	<div class="span6 offset3">
		<p>
			Add a note in here saying your username should make you
			completely anonymous.
		</p>
		<p>
			Add expandable boxes to provide more information on each of these fields. Such as "Username needs to be all lowercase, less than 30 characters, some good examples are", "Password needs to be at least 6 characters long".
		</p>
		<p>
			Add in the JavaScript and jQuery to count how many characters are left.
		</p>
		<p>
			Make it so Password can't be blank doesn't show up twice. Also, if possible remove it from the top errors are printed in the right order.
		</p>
		<%= form_for(@user) do |f| %>
			<%= render 'shared/error_messages', object: f.object %>

			<%= f.label :name, "Username" %>
			<%= f.text_field :name %>

			<%= f.label :password %>
			<%= f.password_field :password %>

			<%= f.label :password_confirmation, "Confirmation" %>
			<%= f.password_field :password_confirmation %>

			<%= f.submit "Create my account", class: "btn btn-large btn-primary" %>
		<% end %>
	</div>
</div>
